review_blob:
This is not going to win any awards for taste. It is a cheap low strength can from Lidl. However it does win well when you want something cheap and cold and not too alcoholic in the middle of summer. This works well even after sauna and is better than that reindeer urine we have called Lapin Kulta. At the price for what you get it is a good deal as long as you manage your expectations ahead of time. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Reasonable beer if not immediately memorable. Difficult to get overly shrouded by its sheer taste and beauty but one would not turn it away in favour of some ghastly English chemical lager either. No real fault but a tad meh. I need to buy another bottle to test if this was a one off. B

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A bit of a cloudy beer that was not an instant hit but it sorts of grows on you with each sip. Incredibly gassy and frothy upon opening despite standing still for a few weeks but once exposed to the air it soon settles down. Taste is reasonably good and slightly bitter or tarty which suits my taste buds. No special memorable flavours stay on the palate but equally it is not offensive. A bit of an acquired taste for many but it does make a change from the filtered similar lookalike breweries that hang on the coT tails of quality German brewing. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This was a nice random find. Reasonably colour even though I don't get hung up on this. A nice bittery taste for a Germanic beer. Not overly smell rich or maybe i must try another bottle to be sure. In any case it was a nice session beer that I could see added to my short list for future acquisitions when one wants something known rather than a random test. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

An interesting find and test. Quite gassy upon opening despite it sitting on the shelf for weeks. A little anemic colour when poured but there was no gassy taste which is confusing. If you like the more bitter type British beers you may like this and it was certainly something one could take as a regular companion. No complex flavours to wax about but equally not a chemical soup. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Just when you think that Lapin can't get worse. Disappointing toilet water colour. No real taste or distinguishing feature other than it is not as metallic as the other Lapin 'urine' beer. One does not want to admit to being Finnish with beer like this. Lidl's cheapest beer is way better than this. This is a chemical soup with colouring. Eww 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Lapin Kulta Arctic Malt Dark Lager

review_blob:
Reasonable start. Slightly sour and bitter taste but pleasant. Fairly good after taste but a little gassy !! Pardon me! Not a strong taste of alcohol but nonetheless not a bad glass. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Reasonably clear but gassy bottle. Nice unspecific taste that is moreish. Maybe would not be an art beer but a good session companion. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Surprisingly more ish. Clear lager that generates a somewhat subtle but slightly gassy taste. But enjoyable and something one could easily spend an evening in its company. A nice session beer that might be potent as the evening develops. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Quite a nice taste but a slight gassy feeling. After taste is pleasant and something you could easily spend an evening with. Caramelish and a nice bitter taste for a lager. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
A reasonable drink with a nice generic flavour. Hard to isolate specific flavours but a fairly good after taste. Very moreish. ---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A little disappointing drink with average quite unspecialised taste. Tastes like a generic beer lacking in character. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not the clearest of beers which looks like poor home brew fortunately it made up for things in taste. No banana taste but slightly sweet whilst retaining a pleasant buttery and bittery taste. I could drink this again if the first bottle is a good indication. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Definitely a novelty beer for me. Little sweet cheery taste but not fully developed. Not offensive but not so moreish either although it might be best described as unformed and diluted with a slight tang. Now I have tried it I would not rush to it again. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Quite a nice smell when opened. Reasonable taste and not gassy. The taste itself is not so strong or developed but it it by no means offensive and a relatively pleasant after taste is there in any event. Manage your expectations but a drink I'd take again. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob:
Warning for much froth when a settled bottle is opened. This is a reasonable if not slightly gassy light session beer. First taste was a little sour but the next mouthful went down without a problem. It gets better as it goes on. Not so strong smell but certainly it helps a thirst and it does not have that metallic taste that some cheaper beers can have. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A clear basic pilsner that fortunately is relatively cheap. No great winner of smell but a taste that develops as you drink. A session beer that will quench your thirst but it probably won't be a winner if you wish to push the boat out. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob:
Very disappointing. When I read another review saying it poured out like river water I thought that was a joke. Sadly not. It reminds me of home brew that has not got it right and it has nearly a year left according to the bottle's date. Disappointing, a bit like poor English beer from the 70s. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A deceptively light beer but still relatively tasty as a refresher. Very frothy when opened from bottle but clean looking. No strong taste elements but equally inoffensive. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Reasonably nice British bitter in a bottle that helps when you are overseas and don't have access to it on cask. Nice bitter after taste. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A little bit of a disappointment as one expected possibly too much. Interesting aroma when opened that did not fully translate to the taste. One of those things to taste to say one has done it but not likely to be a regular partner. A bit falsely sweet rather than a real taste combination. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

High expectations but not fully transferred to reality. Capable of being a good session beer and certainly taste grows after the first sip. Not so strong initial smell or sensory explosion though. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
